Entries.DialogueText: Awwwww, you got me a birthday gift? Well, I really like it!
*gasp*... You got this for me? Wow, , this is the best birthday gift ever!
Gross! You got me this on my birthday? What's wrong with you!
Wow, they're beautiful! These are my absolute favorite.
0.8Mmm.... coconuts remind me of warm, sunny days at the beach. When I hold one, I feel like I'm there... even when it's raining.
For me? Ooooh... I can't decide if I should drink it, or use it as shampoo...
Agh!
Oh... hmph. Beat me to it, huh? Alright...
My name means 'field of hay', but I like to imagine it as a meadow full of sunflowers...
I was waiting for you to ask me that.
You look really handsome today.
You look really pretty today.
So, what's the idea here... am I just going to be your 'girlfriend' forever...?
I'll be fine on my own...
Thanks for the memories.
Why are you still clinging to me? Go live your own life.
Things didn't work out between you and Emily, huh? Well... It happens.
It *is* kind of awkward that you're both still living in this tiny town, though.
I've got nothing to say to you!
No, you won't! This bracelet was passed down to me by my great-grandmother!
*sigh*
...Maybe it'll wash up on another shore. I can't bear to think of it at the bottom of the ocean.
*sigh*...
NO!! I'm not going to do it!
You guys are both stupid!
She should take the 'high road'? What's that supposed to mean?
You think I'm being a baby, huh?
Aw, thanks!
Oh! I thought you knew.
This room's for developing photos.
Is that so...?
Great, then you shouldn't have any problem opening this jar for me!
Oh... you aren't? Hmmm...
Well could you try opening this jar for me anyways?
Him? No!
...Well, I guess I used to like Alex. But not anymore! He's immature.
What? That sounds fun, but I wouldn't want to leave Stardew Valley right now...
Huh? What's an android?
The other day, Emily baked something called a 'squirrel loaf'...
How'd it taste? Um... well, if my tail was a little bushier I probably would've loved it.
Did you see last night's episode of 'Tears'? *sob*... I can't believe Kyle and Amy broke up...
Wow, looks like someone's read the latest issue of 'Super Fashion Girl'... muddy boots are totally in right now!
My parents sent another postcard... I guess they're in the middle of a cruise down the Gem Sea Coast.
They said me and Emily could join them at any point, but let's be honest... who wants to go on vacation with their parents?
greets you with a smile. You notice that she's wearing her Great-Grandma's bracelet.
It was fun taking pictures, but I had to shower for two hours to get the mud out of my hair!
It's fall already?
Is that a grass stain on your knee?
Sorry, I'm allergic to grass.
You look like you've been doing a lot of hard work.
Why don't you take the rest of the day off?
It's gross when all these fallen leaves get slimy.
, I'm happy to see you today.
48#Did I ever tell you I found another one of my great-grandma's bracelets in the attic?|See this bracelet? It belonged to my great-grandmother.
She was a really interesting lady.
It's too cold to go to the beach anymore.*sigh*...what do you think I should do today?Watercolor paintingRelax and read a magazineStop being a selfish crybaby
Hmm... That's a pretty good idea, actually.
Get away from me, you stupid jerk.
I'll probably take a nap later.
I've never been to the forest. It's muddy and I could get a blister on my foot.
I've never been to the forest, you know.
It might be interesting to explore it some day.
I feel the urge to go shopping. *sigh*
Shopping just doesn't sound as fun as it used to.
What's happening to me?
Hmm...
Hmm... Something smells weird...
You've been working on the farm, huh?
Something smells earthy...
Oh, right. You work on a farm.
I'm starting to like the smell of dirt. Isn't that weird?
I think it's because you're around all the time.
Oh, hi. Did you want something?
If you're ever bored, come say hi.
Oh... you want to dance with *me*, do you?
Oh? Sure! I'll dance with you!
Hehe... of course. I'd love to be your partner.
We'll have a great time!
Hmm... I admire your confidence. Most guys are too shy to ask me.
You look so pretty today!
*sigh*... My days of being Flower Queen are over... so it's a bittersweet dance for me.
But, yes...
Ew... No.
is ignoring you.
, can we go on a camping trip someday?
The most exotic place I've been is Zuzu city.
Don't you get tired of running around on that farm all day, or whatever it is you do?
I couldn't stand getting all dirty like that.
You probably get a nice tan, though.
I need to find some kind of hobby other than shopping.
I've decided I want to expand my horizons.
Maybe I should learn to play the mini-harp?
I don't think I've ever set foot in this place. It's actually kind of cozy!
Oh, I'm not worried about the rain. I'm sure it'll pass.
Wake me up when there's a pink rain... Or better yet, a pink cake rain!
Oh... you're that new farmer boy, aren't you?
Oh... You're that new farmer girl, or whatever. Aren't you?
Huh? Oh... I'm Haley.
Hmm... If it weren't for those horrendous clothes you might actually be cute.
Hmm... If it weren't for those horrendous clothes you might actually be pretty... Actually, never mind.
Well, I guess this makes you my 'brother-in-law', huh? That's funny to think about.
Hey, I guess we're kind of like sisters now!
Is Emily settling into the farm life?
You know, I was starting to wonder if Emily would ever get married...
This town is so small. It sucks.
I have to drive, like, twenty miles to buy any decent clothes.
That's why I usually just order online.
What?
I used to complain about this town being so small, but I've grown to like it.
If it was much bigger it wouldn't feel like a community.
This is such a perfect beach. I'd stay here forever if I could!
Gus made a cute, fruity drink just for me!
I painted my toenails blue to match the sea. What do you think? *wiggle* *wiggle*
I saw a dolphin on the way in!
There's something about the sun that just makes me feel good.
It's strange the places life can take you... who knows what other lands are out there?
Wow, look at how the sunlight sparkles on the horizon!
I bet the sunsets here would make for an amazing photo.
I have to remember to bring my camera next time.
Getting the perfect tan is an art form...
It's kind of like toasting a marshmallow... you have to rotate the body just right.
Laying out on a tropical beach.
*sigh* I think I've finally found my place in the universe.
But I guess Stardew Valley's not such a bad place either!
Emily's friend had this swimsuit shipped to me from all the way out in Zuzu City.
City fashion is on a whole different level, isn't it?
I'm feeling an urge to go shopping. Ugh! I wish there was a mall here.
Yesterday I found a seagull with her wing caught in a net. I set her free, of course. She looked so helpless, the poor thing.
You know, I should probably start exercising more... this youthful metabolism won't last forever.
Alright, alright... I'm done giving you the cold shoulder. Just promise me you'll never, ever lie to me again.
Do you have baby bunnies on your farm? Bunnies are SO cute!
I wonder what Alex is doing today...
Huh? I didn't notice you standing there.
Oh, hi !
Do you like kids?
I spent 3 hours practicing my signature today.
I guess that's pretty silly, huh?
I'm going to get such a nice tan this summer.
I should start reading some books instead of magazines.
It's good to learn things, isn't it?
I only ever look at the pictures.
Farming sounds so boring...What do you even do all day?Care for plantsExplore the cavesSnoop around in your roomDig for treasure
Hmm... sounds like a lot of work.
What? You'd better not be doing that!
Hey, you better not be snooping around in my room anymore!|But I guess it could get you in pretty good shape.
It seems like a good day to go swimming.
Emily usually cooks dinner... But she makes weird stuff like quinoa.
I talked to my sister for a while last night. I actually enjoyed it quite a bit.
You know, Emily's not actually that weird. I guess we have more in common than I used to think.
Don't tell her I said so.
If you stay in the sun a lot it'll make your hair lighter.
It's a good thing to know!
If you stay in the sun a lot it will make your hair lighter... But you don't want to get sunburnt, either.
I just want a healthy amount of sunlight. Everything in moderation, right?
Ew, you're all dirty.
Do you wear those clothes every day?
47#Hey I found this new tool to open jars with. So you won't need to help me anymore.|There's not a cloud in the sky today.
I guess living in the country isn't so bad.
If I lived in the city I might start to miss all the trees.
, I think I've been hanging out with you too much.
Um... Yes?
I didn't hear you, I'm thinking about something else.
It's so hot today!
I wish I had some ice cream.
My sister is so weird. Sometimes I wonder if we're actually related.
I'm thinking about donating a bunch of clothes... I must have a hundred pairs of shoes.
I've decided I am going to organize my clothes today. I'll have to throw out all of last year's styles to make room for the new ones!
*sigh* I could really go for a cupcake right now.
Do you need something?
I cooked dinner last night. It actually turned out okay!
But I did make a huge mess in the kitchen...
Nice shoes.
Nice makeup.
Are those made out of plastic?
Or wait... Are you even wearing any?
I'm bored.
I wonder if any nice shells washed up on the beach this morning?
This isn't the best time of year for shells, though.
The only thing I like about this town is the beach.
I'm glad that the flowers are starting to bloom.
Those pink ones smell so good.
There are only two things I like about this town.
One of them is the beach.
The other one is a secret! *giggle*
Hmm. What brand is your shirt?
Oh. Um, never mind.
Do you have a pony on your farm?
Oh. That's disappointing...
Do you think you'll ever have a pony on your farm?
I want to move somewhere warmer.
I wish it were warmer here in Stardew Valley.
I could move somewhere else, but...
The only good thing about winter is that I get to sleep more.
I like at least 10 hours of sleep every night.
I'm glad you have less work to do in the winter.
It must be nice to have a break, huh?
Will you say hi to Alex for me?
Thanks.
, you look rugged today. I like it.
, you look pretty today.
Um, if you see Alex could you tell him I'm busy today?
I'm going to start writing a list of all the clothes I need for next spring.
Maybe I'll donate some of my skirts to a charity this spring.
I mean, I do have over 1,000 skirts.
...what?
Hi. Do you need something from me?
Your name is , right?
I keep forgetting.
Hi .
Is anything exciting happening on your farm?
I wish someone would bring me a peppermint coffee.
Don't even bother, I know you won't be able to make one.
I think I'm starting to realize that clothes aren't the most important thing. Right?
I still like clothes, though. I mean, what's wrong with expressing yourself a little?
I'm so happy!
It's just like I always dreamed.
It's okay. I know we can't have a honeymoon, since your farm needs to be taken care of.
I'm a farmer now, too!
! Come here, quick!
My bracelet is gone! I know I had it on when I got here...
But now it's gone and I can't find it anywhere...
48 null 48 -30 Event_beach1 48 50 Event_beach2#I'm really sorry...
Sorry, Great-Grandma. I lost your precious bracelet. Please forgive me.
Is that...?
You found it!
Thank you so much, . You're a lifesaver.
I won't forget what you did for me here.
Could she have dropped it nearby?
I really owe you one, .
Hi, honey.
Hey... I have an idea... I want to get everyone together for a charity cake-walk.
Uh... It's kind of like musical chairs, but everyone wins and gets cake! You'll see...
It'll be on the next sunny day in the town square.
Um... would you mind bringing a chocolate cake?
Great! I'll meet you in the town square tomorrow, weather permitting.
What's up with the snarky attitude?
Fine. You're going to show up tomorrow with a chocolate cake, or else you're in the dog house. You like that better?
I'm bringing a pink cake.
Oh! .
The lighting is so nice right now... I had to come out and take some nature shots.
I've been trying to connect with the outdoors a little more...
I wanna know what it's like, being a farmer. It's a way of life I've never really thought about.
Well, until now...
Heh, these cows are so cute...
Hey, I have an idea!
Let's take some pictures with these cows! You can show me how to approach one.
I'll just set it to shoot on a timer.
*giggle*
That was fun, ! ...And these photos are hilarious!
I'm gonna go home and take a shower now...
Well, that was the dirtiest I've ever been.
Urgghh! I always clean under the cushions! It's YOUR turn this week!
Oh, it's that new ${farm boy
girl from the farm}$.
Hey, I bet you'll understand my point of view here.
45 null 46 -50 Event_clean2 45 30 Event_clean1 46 -30 Event_clean3#Emily, take the high road and do it this time.
Alright, you win. I guess this can be my job every week. Then there won't be any reason to argue over it.
Nnnnnghhh... I just can't get this jar open!
Oh! It's you..., right?
47 null 47 30 Event_jar1 47 -30 Event_jar2#No
Hey, you did it! You're stronger than you look!
Thanks!
Come in! Just make sure to close the door quickly behind you!
, you're here!
Welcome to my brand new dark room!
-1 null -1 10 Event_darkroom1 -1 0 Event_darkroom2 -1 -50 Event_darkroom3#I've seen better.
Um... so, anyway... what do you want to do?
Oh, ... I've been waiting so long for you to do that.
One moment...
Make an excuse and leave.#Try to kiss her.
That was nice...

Entries.DialogueText: Not so fast!

Entries.DialogueText: Hi!

Entries.DialogueText: It was an uneventful gathering!
...I think we've come to a decision... isn't that right, girls?
I doubt it...
Liar!
Pierre pressured me! He wanted to sell more bouquets!#Ladies, this is completely normal! It's just a lifestyle choice...
Hey! Oh, good, you brought the cake!...
Seems really moist. Thanks, .
Next up, Jodi. You're gonna take home...
Emily's organic red velvet cake... colored with beets!
...and last, but not least: Pam! You're the lucky winner of my husband's deluxe chocolate cake.
...and last, but not least: Pam! You're the lucky winner of my wife's deluxe chocolate cake.
Thanks everyone for joining in. We raised over 5,000g!
Actually... it's for Penny.
Penny, the other day I overheard you talking with Jas and Vincent about their school books. It sounded like you could use some help...
It's a pretty good turnout, huh?
Whoops! Forgot to blow the whistle.
Alright! Everyone should be standing on a numbered square.
Your number determines which cake you win!
Okay, let's see who gets what...
Okay, Let's see here...
Caroline, what number are you? Okay... you've won...
Mayor Lewis' cave carrot loaf... with extra fiber!
Emily, you've got...
Pam's chocolate stout cupcakes, with aged bourbon buttercream.
Next... Jas, you've got...
Clint's wild horseradish cobbler.
Uh, Okay... Next up is Vincent. We've got...
Robin's Triple syrup n' cream strawberry sugar log!
Emily tried to serve me {1} {2} for dinner last night... I threw it away when she wasn't looking.
I don't like health food...
*giggle*... "/faceDirection farmer 1 true/emote farmer 8/pause 1000/speak Haley "Oh, it's just that...
As a little girl, I always dreamed that one day, I would climb to the summit with my true love, and share a kiss."
Did you remember to bring good stuff for our grange display? I hope we win this year.
Have you been to the fortune teller? She set up her stand in the graveyard.I already saw her... she told me something... interesting. *giggle*
It's a little funny seeing Alex stuff his face. He seems to be doing well.I hope we win the grange display contest this year!
I'm trying to maintain a diet this fall... but I can't resist these juicy burgers!
I get scared easily... I think I'm just going to stay right here.
Eek! I'm too scared.
Hah! None of this is real..... right, ? It's not real... right?
Have you seen my sister?Emily! Can you hear me?
I was going to eat some eggs, but then I remembered I'm on a spring diet.
This festival is alright... but what I'm really looking forward to is the Flower Dance.
Oh! I still need to get my photo taken at the bunny stand. Does my hair look okay?
I'm practicing my dance moves... It needs to be perfect.I've been flower queen for the past 5 years and I'm not ready to step off the throne just yet!
Today is the big day! We'll be the centerpiece of the whole dance!
One, two, three... one, two, three... Oh, hi. I'm a little busy.
Phew... I'm afraid to move, or else I might start to sweat.
I would dance, but I don't want to get sweaty.
I'm tempted to run back home and grab my bikini.The water's at a perfect temperature... I dipped my little toe in!
Don't block the sun! I'm in just the right spot to avoid getting any tan lines.
I'm gonna take a picture of the jellies when they arrive.
Aww... It's so romantic, with all the candles.Goodbye, Summer...
I didn't have time to put on makeup... Do you think anyone would notice in the dark?
Me?... Oh, I'm thankful for... how about I just show you when we get home tonight?
I hope there's a new camera for me under the spirit tree!
When I count all the good things in my life, I feel like I've been blessed by the Winter Star.
It's so pretty... I wish our town could always look like this!
Brr... my hands are freezing from making this snowman.
I guess Winter isn't all bad... playing in the snow can be fun!
Come here, let me fix your hair... I'm going to take an action shot of you during the contest!
I'm glad I wore earmuffs, it's freezing out here!I brought my camera this year. It's perfect lighting for a winter photoshoot!
Oh my god, this is my favorite thing!!
*gasp*...for me? Thank you!
Ugh...that's such a stupid gift.
Gross!
Thank you. I love presents.
